
[1]neptunian

   NEPTUNIAN, a. [the fabled deity of the ocean.]

   1. Pertaining to the ocean or sea.

   2. Formed by water or aqueous solution; as Neptunian rocks.

    NEPTUNIAN, n. One who adopts the theory that the whole earth was once
     covered with water, or rather that the substances of the globe were
        formed from aqueous solution; opposed to the Plutonic theory.
     __________________________________________________________________

